  "texts": [
    "This search strategy identified a corpus of 52 Oncogene papers that commonly described the analysis of one or more miR's and/or circRNAs (Table 2).",
    "Most (42/52, 81%) selected Oncogene papers described human research and at least one nucleotide sequence that was claimed to target a nonmodified human gene or genomic sequence.",
    "These 42 papers described a median number of 20 sequences/paper (range 2-115) (Table 2).",
    "The 42 Oncogene papers included 1165 nucleotide sequences, of which 47 (4.0%) sequences were predicted to be wrongly identified (Table 2, Table S1).",
    "These 47 wrongly identified sequences were distributed across 21/52 (40%) corpus papers and 21/42 (50%) screened papers (Table S2)."
